SIMPLE: setter
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Setter
<hw>Set"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, sets; -- used mostly in composition with a noun, as
type<xex>setter</xex>; or in combination with an adverb, as a
<xex>setter</xex> on (or inciter), a <xex>setter</xex> up, a
<xex>setter</xex> forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A hunting dog of a special breed
originally derived from a cross between the spaniel and the pointer.
Modern setters are usually trained to indicate the position of game
birds by standing in a fixed position, but originally they indicated it
by sitting or crouching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are several distinct varieties of setters; as, the
<xex>Irish</xex>, or <xex>red</xex>, <xex>setter</xex>; the <xex>Gordon
setter</xex>, which is usually red or tan varied with black; and the
<xex>English setter</xex>, which is variously colored, but usually white
and tawny red, with or without black.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who hunts victims for sharpers.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who adapts words to music in
composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An adornment; a decoration; -- with
<xex>off</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They come as . . . <qex>setters</qex> off of thy graces.</q>
<rj><qau>Whitlock.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Pottery)</fld> <def>A shallow seggar for
porcelain.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Setter
<hw>Set"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cut the dewlap (of a cow or
an ox), and to insert a seton, so as to cause an issue.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setterwort</ent>⟦br⟧
